The <b>Banded Quail</b> (<i>Philortyx fasciatus</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Odontophoridae" title="Odontophoridae" class="mw-redirect">Odontophoridae</a> family. It is found only in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>.
Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a>, subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shrubland" title="Shrubland">shrubland</a>, subtropical or tropical high-altitude shrubland, and heavily degraded former forest.
